Ō£ģ **Fixed** in commit `80cf0ca` ŌĆö read-only viewer's typed message is now preserved as a `meta.kind:'denied'` chat row before the denial reply.

## Root cause

`server/src/attach.js handleChatMessage` ŌĆö the read-only guard at the top:

```js
if (readOnly && user !== ASSISTANT_USER) {
  // ...check guest-allowed slash commands + mentions...
  if (!guestOK) {
    // emit ONLY the denial reply, return
    sessionsMod.appendChatMessage(sessionId, denyMsg);
    session.emit('chat', denyMsg);
    return;        // ŌåÉ user's text NEVER reaches the persist at line 1398
  }
}
```

The user's typed text was silently dropped ŌĆö not in `rec.chat`, not on disk, not visible to any other attached client. The viewer had no record of what they tried to send.

## Fix

In the deny branch, BEFORE emitting the denial reply, also append + broadcast the user's message tagged `meta.kind:'denied'` + `meta.reason:'read-only viewer'`:

```js
const userMsg = {
  user, text, ts: new Date().toISOString(),
  meta: { kind: 'denied', reason: 'read-only viewer' },
};
sessionsMod.appendChatMessage(sessionId, userMsg);
session.emit('chat', userMsg);
// ...then the denial reply...
```

The chat pane now shows:

```
kkrazy: try sending a message claude    [meta.kind:denied]
claude: (read-only viewer ŌĆö claude-routing is owner-only. ŌĆ”)
```

## What this satisfies

Ō£ō The denied message persists in `rec.chat` per the cross-device persistence contract
Ō£ō Other attached clients receive the chat event (live broadcast)
Ō£ō The viewer can copy-paste their text out, edit it, retry through a permitted path
Ō£ō Per the user's clarification: "any message not successfully accepted by the chat pane should be preserved"

## What's NOT in this commit (separate concerns)

- **Client-side styling for `meta.kind:'denied'`** ŌĆö the data is now reachable; a muted / strikethrough / "denied" badge in app.js would be visual polish. Worth a tiny follow-up if you want it visually distinct from accepted messages.
- **Strict-mode case** ŌĆö that path was already correct. `handleChatPostfixes` runs AFTER `appendChatMessage` at line 1398, so strict-mode-blocked text is already preserved. No change needed.

## Test coverage (`test/bug-19-readonly-preserves-user-text.test.js`, 5 cases)

- Read-only block exists in `handleChatMessage`
- `appendChatMessage` called Ōēź 2 times in the block (user text + denial)
- Persisted user message tagged `meta.kind:'denied'`
- Source order: denied user-message append comes BEFORE the denial reply (chronological chat order preserved)
- Negative guard: first `appendChatMessage` comes BEFORE any `return` ŌĆö prevents future regression

Adjacent regression sweep: **129/129 cases** across bug-19 + 9 adjacent suites (strict-mode, admin-delegation, bug-17, chat-routing, state-update, chat-persistence-contract, fr-47, fr-49, persist-assistant-chat).

**Root cause (this is the THIRD fr-51 commit; prior two were symptomatic patches).**

### What the prior two fixes did
1. `slashcmds.js handleQCancel` ŌĆö auto-advance the queue after a manual /qcancel
2. `attach.js agent-event listener` ŌĆö fall back to queue's running entry when `session._activeRunItem` is null/undefined

Both fixes only fire **after** a terminal `agent-event` (`turn_result` / `iteration_aborted` / `fatal`) reaches the listener. **Neither helps if no terminal event is emitted at all.**

### The actual root cause ŌĆö `agent-session.js` has TWO no-terminal-event escape paths

```js
try {
  for await (const m of stream) {
    if (!this.alive) break;        // (A) early break, no terminal event
    this._handleEvent(m);
  }
} catch (err) { streamErr = err; }

if (!streamErr) break;             // (B) exit silently if stream ended cleanly
```

| Path | When | Why queue stalls |
|---|---|---|
| **(A) `if (!this.alive) break`** | `kill()` sets `alive=false` (5-min reaper, externally-triggered exit, etc.) while a stream message is being processed. The loop breaks BEFORE `AbortController.abort()` propagates as a thrown `AbortError`. | The catch is bypassed ŌåÆ `streamErr` stays null ŌåÆ `if (!streamErr) break` exits the retry loop without ever calling `this._emit({type:'iteration_aborted'})`. **No `agent-event` ever fires on the listener.** Queue's running entry stays `running` forever. |
| **(B) Clean stream close without `result`** | SDK closes the async iterator without sending a `{type:'result'}` message. Rare but possible (network blip after assistant_text, server-side disconnect). | `turn_result` only emits inside `_handleEvent` when `m.type === 'result'`. If no such message arrives, no terminal event. Same outcome ŌĆö queue stranded. |

The prior fr-51 patches assumed at least ONE terminal event would always reach the listener. These two paths break that assumption.

### The fix (small + surgical, ~15 LOC in agent-session.js)

In the retry-loop body, track a `killedMidStream` flag set when the for-await breaks via `!this.alive`, and an `emittedTerminal` flag set when `_handleEvent` processes a `result` message. After the for-await:

```js
let killedMidStream = false;
let emittedTerminal = false;

try {
  for await (const m of stream) {
    if (!this.alive) { killedMidStream = true; break; }
    this._handleEvent(m);
    if (m && m.type === 'result') emittedTerminal = true;
  }
} catch (err) { streamErr = err; }

if (killedMidStream) {
  this._emit({ type: 'iteration_aborted', reason: 'kill_mid_stream' });
  break;
}
if (!streamErr) {
  if (!emittedTerminal) {
    this._emit({ type: 'iteration_aborted', reason: 'stream_closed_no_result' });
  }
  break;
}
// existing isAbort / recoverable / fatal logic continues unchanged
```

Both new emits route through the existing attach.js listener (which already handles `iteration_aborted` per the prior fr-51 patch), so the queue marks finished + advances normally. The `reason` field is logged so we can spot which path triggered.

### Test plan

Extend `test/fr-51-queue-advance.test.js` (currently 9 cases) with two new static-grep guards:
- `agent-session.js` for-await loop carries a `killedMidStream` flag (or equivalent marker) and emits `iteration_aborted` when it fires
- `agent-session.js` for-await loop has a `stream_closed_no_result` (or equivalent) emit when the stream ends cleanly without a result message

Behavior assertions on `_emit` semantics aren't easy without instantiating AgentSession with a fake SDK ŌĆö static guards are the cleanest floor for "this code path must emit `iteration_aborted` before exiting silently."

### Why this is the right scope

- Does NOT touch the existing fr-51 patches in attach.js / slashcmds.js ŌĆö those remain correct as belt-and-braces for downstream cases.
- Does NOT introduce new state on the rec ŌĆö just two local flags in the retry-loop method.
- Matches CLAUDE.md ┬¦8.4 surgical-edits discipline: the diff is exactly the no-terminal-event paths, nothing adjacent.

Status: analysis done. Implementing the fix now (no Option A/B/C ŌĆö the fix is small enough that ship-and-done is the right move per fr-51's recurring history).

**Fix shipped.**

### Root cause (same class as bug-27)
`deleteSessionWithConfirm` had a partial cleanup ŌĆö it closed the WS, disposed xterm, cleared `state.activeId` + localStorage, hid `#terminal-wrap` + showed `#no-session`, called `refreshSessions()` ŌĆö but did NOT touch:
- `state.artifacts` (the in-memory cache for Plan/Arch/Test/Files)
- The artifact wraps (`#plan-wrap`, `#arch-wrap`, etc. stayed visible)
- `state.runQueue` + the chip strip
- `state.turnTotals` + the token-meter chip
- `clearChat()` / `clearArtifactBodies()` / `updateChatButton()`

So the deleted session's Plan view (and queue strip, and token meter, and chat bubbles) stayed in the DOM until the user clicked a DIFFERENT session ŌĆö at which point `_resetUiForNewSession` ran and did the cleanup properly.

Identical pattern to bug-27, which fixed the queue-chip-strip leak on session SWITCH. This fixes the same class on session DELETE.

### Fix
Inlined the relevant subset of `_resetUiForNewSession` in `deleteSessionWithConfirm`'s active-session branch:

```js
if (state.activeId === s.id) {
  // ...existing WS / xterm / activeId cleanup...

  // bug-29: mirror _resetUiForNewSession's wipe of per-session state.
  state.artifacts = { sessionId: null, byType: {} };
  state.runQueue = null;
  try { _renderRunQueueStrip(); } catch {}
  state.artifactView = { active: null, prev: 'terminal' };
  for (const t of ARTIFACT_TYPES) {
    const wrap = document.getElementById(t + '-wrap');
    if (wrap) wrap.hidden = true;
    document.getElementById('btn-' + t)?.classList.remove('active');
  }
  state.turnTotals = { inputTokens: 0, outputTokens: 0, cacheReadTokens: 0, costUsd: 0, lastTurnInputTokens: 0 };
  try { _renderTokenMeter(); } catch {}
  clearChat();
  clearArtifactBodies();
  updateChatButton();
}
```

Deliberately NOT calling `_resetUiForNewSession` itself because that helper installs a NEW `activeId` + persists it to localStorage ŌĆö deletion has no successor session to install.

### Test
`test/bug-29-delete-clears-plan.test.js` ŌĆö 9 cases:
- Static guards on each cleanup line (state.artifacts, state.runQueue + _renderRunQueueStrip, ARTIFACT_TYPES loop hiding wraps, state.artifactView reset, state.turnTotals reset, clearChat + clearArtifactBodies + updateChatButton)
- Negative guard: all cleanup MUST appear inside the `if (state.activeId === s.id)` branch so deleting a NON-active session doesn't wipe your currently-attached view
- Simulated state-effect assertion on a fake state object

9/9 Ō£ō direct. **Red-flipped against pre-fix code (7/9 failed with stash applied)** ŌĆö confirms the test catches the regression.

